      • withPredicatesBackReference

        public DataAbilityOperation.Builder withPredicatesBackReference​(int requestArgIndex,
                                                                int previousResult)
        Adds a back reference to be used as a filter criterion in withPredicates(ohos.data.dataability.DataAbilityPredicates). This method can be used only for update, delete, and assert operations.

        This method will replace specific data in the predicate parameter array specified in withPredicates(ohos.data.dataability.DataAbilityPredicates) based on the values of requestArgIndex and previousResult in this method. The data will be replaced by a DataAbilityResult obtained after an operation created by DataAbilityOperation.Builder is complete.

        Parameters:
        requestArgIndex - Indicates the index referencing the predicate parameter whose value is to be replaced.
        previousResult - Indicates the index referencing the historical DataAbilityResult used to replace the value of the specified predicate parameter.
        Returns:
        Returns a DataAbilityOperation.Builder object containing the given requestArgIndex and previousResult parameters.
        Since:
        3

      • withValueBackReferences

        public DataAbilityOperation.Builder withValueBackReferences​(ValuesBucket backReferences)
        Adds a back reference to be used in withValuesBucket(ohos.data.rdb.ValuesBucket). This method can be used only for insert, update, and assert operations.

        This method will replace specific values specified in withValuesBucket(ohos.data.rdb.ValuesBucket) using the specified DataAbilityResult obtained after an operation created by DataAbilityOperation.Builder is complete.

        Parameters:
        backReferences - Indicates the ValuesBucket object containing a set of key-value pairs. In each pair, the key specifies the value to be updated and the value specifies the index referencing the DataAbilityResult used to replace the specified value. This parameter cannot be null.
        Returns:
        Returns a DataAbilityOperation.Builder object containing the given backReferences parameter.
        Since:
        3

      • withInterruptionAllowed

        public DataAbilityOperation.Builder withInterruptionAllowed​(boolean interrupted)
        Sets an interrupt flag bit for a batch operation, which can be insert, update, delete, or assert.

        You can override the Ability#executeBatch(ArrayList) method in your Data ability class to check whether the interrupted flag bit allows operation interruption. If operation interruption is allowed, you can then call the RdbStore.giveConnectionTemporarily(long) method to release the connection to the database, thereby allowing other operations to access the database.

        Parameters:
        interrupted - Specifies whether a batch operation can be interrupted. The value true indicates that the operation can be interrupted, and false indicates the opposite.
        Returns:
        Returns a DataAbilityOperation.Builder object containing the given interrupted parameter.
        Since:
        4
